Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine light red-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 201, 51? Name Kleisimbrotos. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, 0370.25.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0516)
